title: Bottle Stopper, ca. 1810
provenance: W. G. T. Burne, London; 1983 WPW
dimensions: H x diam.: 10.2 x 4.2 cm (4 x 1 5/8 in.)
description: Pear-shaped body cut with drapery swags and flat vertical fluting; flat circular foot; mushroom-shaped stopper with radial cutting. One of set of seven bottles.

tombstone.epitaph:
Bottle Stopper, ca. 1810.
ca. 1810. glass. Bequest of Walter Phelps Warren. 1986-61-25-a,b.
